content:
Ah, Denna. The name catches in your throat, like a song half-remembered. A memory of a smile, a flicker of sea-grey eyes, and a lilt of banter which once was. Denna... Wandering and elusive as the wind. And like the wind, you can never hold her;

yet maybe, just maybe, in some unknown place, you might find her. An inn, perhaps, or a hidden corner of a bustling city market.

But here, in the bleak stillness of the crypt? The chances seem slim to none. Yet, hope, like a musician's defiance against a sour note, refuses to fade. So, you move, slowly, guided by the lonely light of your torch, its flickering illumination casting a sense of yearning that mirrors the rhythm of your heart. Each step could be a step closer to her, or a step further into the echoing void of her absence. You are Kvothe, the Flame, the Broken-Hearted, in search of his song... in search of Denna.
